NOTE: You may like to create a backup of this folder before starting!

NOTE: If you are using IPv6 you will need to change any references to localhost in the btconfig.xmlles to be localhost4 or 127.0.0.1

1. SET ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
In order to run the example you need to make sure that you have set the environment
variables HOSTNAME and BLACKTIE_HOME appropriately.
On Linux you need to edit:
	$BLACKTIE_HOME/setenv.sh
On Windows:
	%BLACKTIE_HOME%\setenv.bat
Then, execute the script setenv

2. RUN THE EXAMPLE
This example makes use of maven to build, deploy and test an XATMI service deployed 
as an MDB.

Edit the following files to set REPLACE_WITH_HOSTNAME as appropriate:
	pom.xml

After the dependencies are installed you can then run the example using the following command:
	mvn install
